<p>The more important parts of this letter are printed by <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Edmund C. Burnett, ed., &lt;i&gt;Letters of Members of the Continental Congress&lt;/i&gt; ]">Burnett, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Letters of Members</span></span>, <span class="hi-small-caps" style="font-variant: small-caps;">v</span>, No. 288, and are fully annotated there. See also <a href="default.xqy?keys=TSJN-print-01-03-02-0722" class="document">Huntington to TJ, 10 Sep. 1780</a>, on the problem of western land clams by the states.</p></div>
